We recommended and Management agreed to direct the City Accountant;
a)  To draw the following adjusting entries;
General Fund
Trust Fund
b) To update herself of the latest issuances on accounting and reporting guidelines on government transactions.
c) See to it that all journal entries made shall comply with existing applicable accounting and reporting guidelines to ensure faithful representation of related accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended that Management;
Direct the local health board to furnish the Office of the Auditor the lists of frontline HRHs, and public and private health workers for the grant of COVID-19 AHDP and SRA as determined by them in accordance with Item 4.1 of DBM-DOH Joint Circular Nos 1 & 2, s. 2020 both dated November 25, 2020, for further evaluation of the transactions.
Instruct the City Accountant to strictly approve transactions in accordance with the provisions of applicable laws, rules and regulations to avoid possible suspension/disallowance in audit.

We recommended and Management agreed to direct the Acting CDRRM Officer to;
Update themselves to the latest policies and guidelines on Donations In-Kind as provided by the relevant and competent government offices.
Ensure the one-time preparation and submission of the Report of the Donations, Received, Distributed and Balances to the Office of the Civil Defense and Auditor’s Office, in compliance to Item II (b) of COA Circular No. 2020-009 dated April 21, 2020 to ensure transparency on the use of these additional public funds.

We recommended that Management:
Place safeguarding controls to protect the project in order to prevent further loss or wastage arising from theft, destruction or damage of the property pursuant to Section 2 of PD 1445;
Prioritize the formulation of a concrete plan regarding the construction and completion of the same and allocate funds to fast track the completion of the building to be operational/usable;
In case of construction by phases, ensure that there is a clear delineation of work for each phase up to its completion, which must be usable, and structurally sound pursuant to Item 4, Annex A of RIRR of RA 9184.
Submit the report on the theft incident to the Office of the Auditor for our reference.

