We recommended that Management shall:
a. Ensure that a BAC Resolution is passed for consulting services under the negotiated procurement prior to the perfection of the contract;
b. Establish a standard process for hiring consultants under negotiated contract;
c. Create a committee thru the Human Resource Management Office to oversee the hiring of consultants as well as the evaluation of their capacity to undertake the tasks for which they are being engaged and document the same.

We recommended that management:

a. Require the concerned heads of departments/ offices to prepare and submit the accountability reports to the Local Finance Committee and other oversight bodies to ensure that financial, operational and implementation constraints are immediately addressed; 
b. Require the Local Finance Committee to establish internal performance evaluation standards and conduct semi-annual review of the physical and financial performance of the departments/ offices of the City based on the required accountability reports; 
c. Submit the Performance Review Report on the results of the evaluation with the corresponding recommendations to the City Mayor, Sangguniang Panlungsod and oversight agencies; and
d. Post the Performance Review Report in the city’s website and in publicly accessible and conspicuous places.

We recommended that Management shall:
Ensure that a BAC Resolution is passed for consulting services under the negotiated procurement prior to the perfection of the contract;
Establish a standard process for hiring consultants under negotiated contract;
Create a committee thru the Human Resource Management Office to oversee the hiring of consultants as well as the evaluation of their capacity to undertake the tasks for which they are being engaged and document the same.

We recommended that management:
a. Direct the City Accountant to review the assigned tasks to the designated personnel and if warranted, assigned another staff to handle the preparation of the report to ensure its timely submission to the CDRRMO and other oversight bodies;
b. Direct the City Accountant to instruct her staff handling the report to prepare it monthly;
c. Direct the CDRRM Officer to monitor and evaluate the progress of the implementation of the projects/activities funded by the LDRRMF and to prepare the corresponding report thereon; and
d. Adopt the performance indicator and measures in the NDRRM Plan and develop feedback mechanisms to facilitate the assessment on the progress of the CDRRM plan.
